**The Oread tribal short sword reflects their culture, adorned with markings and symbols denoting their elemental and human heritage. The hilt is wrapped in colorful cloth or braided leather. The sword is used in traditional Oread ceremonies, making it a versatile tool as well as a weapon. It denotes the wearer family heritage and status as an adult. All men (and some women) wear one short sword: warriors of special status wear two. The blade of the short sword is made from a special horn with a natural strength and resilience that Oreads appreciate. The blade of the short sword is made entirely of a single horn, from a powerful creature that the Oread summon from the elemental plane. The horn is polished to a high shine and sharpened to a keen edge, making it both practical and visually striking.** - Upscaled by <@693473644801818724> (fast)

**The great plaid of the Oread mountain people reflects their rugged, yet elegant nature. A heavy, woolen fabric with a deep, earthy palette of greens, browns, and blues evokes the colors of their natural mountainous environment. The plaid pattern itself is bold and geometric, featuring interlocking triangles or diamonds that represent the strength and unity of their community. To add a touch of magic, metallic threads are woven into the fabric to catch the light and sparkle like the precious stones that the Oread people mine from their mountain homes. This plaid material is not only functional for their cold climate but also a proud symbol of their cultural heritage.** - Upscaled (Light) by <@206905492029571074> (fast)
